body:
Trilu has different supporting type for CPUExecutionProvider and CUDAExecutionProvider. Since your target device is GPU, you can try '--use_gpu' option with optimizer script.

It seems that optimizer isn't updated for a change to set an explicit execution provider when creating a session. We'll fix this issue.
@hanbitmyths I've tried the optimizer commands above with the `--use_gpu` flag, I am seeing the same error I've shared.

Hi @mstfbl, you can work around this by modifying this line:https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/blob/0d09dd5d20c3a5133e6e6ae1218cdc45ccaf0358/onnxruntime/python/tools/transformers/optimizer.py#L222 with use_gpu=True and explicitly set cuda ep here:
https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/blob/0d09dd5d20c3a5133e6e6ae1218cdc45ccaf0358/onnxruntime/python/tools/transformers/optimizer.py#L96
then run with --use_gpu flag

> Trilu has different supporting type for CPUExecutionProvider and CUDAExecutionProvider. Since your target device is GPU, you can try '--use_gpu' option with optimizer script.
> 
> It seems that optimizer isn't updated for a change to set an explicit execution provider when creating a session. We'll fix this issue.

I'm a little concerned about this fix: If using cuda ep in optimize_by_onnxruntime(), the exported model will contain "memcpy" and runs only on cuda ep.

issue.title: [models] Ensure all PyTorch models are ONNX exportable

repository.name: doctr
repository.description: docTR (Document Text Recognition) - a seamless, high-performing & accessible library for OCR-related tasks powered by Deep Learning.

issue.body:
Most users of the library are more interested in existing pretrained models to use for inference rather than training. For this reason, it's important to ensure we can easily export those trained models.

- General
    - [x] Add a unittest/CI job to check that all models can be exported with ONNX (#976, #979, #980 )

- Classification
     - [x] VGG (#830)
    - [x] ResNet (#830)
    - [x] MobileNet V3 (#830)
    - [x] MAGC ResNet (#830)

- Text Detection
    - [x] LinkNet #979 
    - [x] DBNet #979 

- Text Recognition
    - [x] CRNN #980 
    - [x] SAR #980 
    - [x] MASTER #980  (#986)
    
    NOTE: master is exportable but in fact of an onnxruntime internal issue (https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/issues/10994) the loading fails
